# MCP-First Org Verification

The Salesforce DX MCP is connected. **Use it by default** — querying the live org directly uses fewer tokens than reading static metadata files or shelling out to the CLI, and it reflects what is actually deployed (local source can be stale).

## Use MCP for
| Task | Tool |
|------|------|
| Verify a field exists; get its API name / type | MCP |
| Check picklist values on a field | MCP |
| Confirm object relationships | MCP |
| Run anonymous Apex to test logic | MCP |
| Inspect deployed metadata (classes, LWC, permissions) | MCP |

## Use the CLI for
| Task | Tool |
|------|------|
| Deploy / retrieve metadata | CLI (`sf project deploy`) |
| Destructive changes | CLI only |
| Upload static resources (if deploy fails) | Manual via Setup UI |

## The rule
Before writing any SOQL, field reference, or Apex class, **confirm the field API name exists in the org via MCP**. Do not trust static metadata files alone — they drift from the deployed org. Target org: `{{ORG_ALIAS}}`.

